Regulation Name(s): Immunoglobulins A, G, M, D, and E immunological test system
Document Summary: FDA 510(k) summary for Yumizen C1200 Immunoglobulin A, G, and M immunoturbidimetric reagents for quantitative measurement of immunoglobulins in serum and lithium heparin plasma on the Yumizen C1200 analyzer.
Indications for Use Summary: Quantitative in vitro diagnostic determination of Immunoglobulin A, G, and M in serum and lithium heparin plasma to aid in diagnosing abnormal protein metabolism and the body's resistance to infectious agents, for use on Yumizen analyzers in conjunction with other laboratory and clinical findings.
